reviews.mitigation:
Avoid reading properties directly from untrusted input objects. Instead, inspect the object's prototype for the constructor reference and access constructor.name from the prototype (which is less likely to invoke user-defined getters). For example:
- const proto = Object.getPrototypeOf(data);
- if (proto && proto !== Object.prototype && proto.constructor) return String(proto.constructor.name);
Also wrap formatting logic in a try/catch to avoid throwing during message construction and consider limiting how much inspection of untrusted objects the formatter performs. Document that parsing the type may inspect prototypes and take care when calling formatters on untrusted inputs.

